\par \pard\plain \s39\rtlch\ai\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf18\i\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\qc\sb480\sa120{\loch
Prepared for organizations subject to NIS2 regulatory obligations}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af6\afs32\ab \ltrch\hich\af2\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb360\sa180\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f2\fs32\b\dbch\af6\pagebb\sb0\sa180{\loch
Executive Summary}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa180{\loch
The NIS2 Directive represents the European Union's most comprehensive cybersecurity regulation to date, directly impacting organizations providing essential and important services across all member states. Unlike voluntary frameworks, NIS2 establishes mandatory minimum security requirements with significant enforcement mechanisms.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af6\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af2\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb240\sa120\keepn\ltrpar\cf17\f2\fs26\b\dbch\af6{\loch
Key Points for Board Consideration}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
Regulatory mandate: }{\loch
NIS2 is law, not a voluntary standard. Compliance is required for in-scope entities.}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
Enforcement timeline: }{\loch
Belgium implemented October 2024; Netherlands expected Q2 2026. Enforcement is imminent.}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
Board accountability: }{\loch
Management bodies are explicitly accountable for oversight and approval of cybersecurity measures.}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
Significant penalties: }{\loch
Up to \u8364\'8010M or 2% of global turnover for essential entities; \u8364\'807M or 1.4% for important entities.}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
24/72-hour incident reporting: }{\loch
Strict notification deadlines to national Computer Security Incident Response Teams (CSIRTs).}
\par \pard\plain \s37\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\listtext\pard\plain  \u8226\'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li720\lin720\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\loch
Implementation timeframe: }{\loch
Realistic compliance requires 6-12 months for most organizations.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af6\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af2\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb240\sa120\keepn\ltrpar\cf17\f2\fs26\b\dbch\af6{\loch
Strategic Opportunity}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa180{\loch
Organizations that approach NIS2 strategically can achieve dual compliance objectives. Approximately 55% of NIS2 requirements overlap with GDPR obligations, and 75% align with ISO 27001 controls. A unified compliance program reduces overall effort while strengthening security posture and demonstrating regulatory diligence.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af6\afs32\ab \ltrch\hich\af2\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb360\sa180\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f2\fs32\b\dbch\af6\pagebb\sb0\sa180{\loch
NIS2 Directive Overview}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af6\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\sb0\sa180{\loch
The Network and Information Security Directive 2 (Directive (EU) 2022/2555) entered into force on January 16, 2023, replacing the original NIS Directive. Member states were required to transpose NIS2 into national law by October 17, 2024.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af6\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af2\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb240\sa120\keepn\ltrpar\cf17\f2\fs26\b\dbch\af6{\loch
Regulatory Objectives}
